Expenditures 2010-12

Adopted Budget 2014-15

columns.name: Ledger Type
columns.description:
General Ledger Description for the posting to the ledger.

Ledger Types are as follows:
B1 = Revised Budget
BA =  Adopted Budget
B2 = Estimated Actual (not used in this report)
AA = Actuals

columns.name: Cost Center Type
columns.description:
This field identifies expenses and budget between operating and capital.

IS = Operating
JB = Capital

columns.name: Fund Description
columns.description: This is Fund Name associated with the Fund Number.

columns.name: Expenditure Category Id
columns.description: This defines the capital expenditures and budget by program category as appears in the budget document.

columns.name: Expenditure Category Description
columns.description: This is the description corresponding to the Expense Category ID.

columns.name: Project ID
columns.description: This identifies the capital project.  The same project id can be used across multiple funds (if funded using multiple sources).

columns.name: Fiscal year
columns.description: This defines the fiscal year . For ex: 2010 is FY July2010 - 2011.

columns.name: June
columns.description: This is the final month of the fiscal year - Period 12.  For this purposes of this report, it includes period 13.  Period 13 is the adjustment period for year-end CAFR related adjustments.
